G-STEEL
700 SERIES

GM-700-1A

NEW 11/2024
MRP
₹ 15,995 (incl. of all taxes)
  • Bio-based resin is used in the case components.
My GShock
Click to Buy
Store Locator (Opens in a new tab)

Introducing the G-STEEL GM-700, the latest in the line of globally popular analog-digital G-SHOCK timepieces featuring the classic big case. Inheriting the solid, fashionable stainless-steel bezel design of the GM-5600, GM-6900, and GM-110, the GM-700 is based on the GA-700, taking it into all-new terrain with a metal bezel in one of three different colors. The silver and gold color bezels highlight the natural bold look of the metals they project. The striking look of the purple-black bezel is achieved with purple accents against black ion plating. The front button design makes it easy to access the LED light to illuminate the dial for a high-visibility, easy read at night and in dark places.

  • Bio-based resin is used in the case components.
  • Shock resistant
  • 20 bar water resistant
  • Easy to see in darkness
  • Bright metallic color

Model Comparison

FEATURES

Impressive beauty in a metal bezel

Stainless steel is used for the bezel. Its complex form, which protects glass and buttons, is crafted with meticulous processes of forging, cutting, and polishing. Separate hairline and mirror finishes are applied to individual surfaces, creating metal exteriors with color IP in a selection of hues setting off the texture of the metal with a striking look of sophistication.

Attention to materials: Bio-based resin

Bio-based resin is used in the case components. Produced using renewable organic resources, the material is expected to help reduce environmental impact.

*The second image is included for illustrative purposes only.

Powerful-looking and easy to read: 3D face

The analog-digital combination dial design gives the watch an impressive sense of depth. The angular form of the components, including the extra thick, powerful-looking watch hands and dimensional index marks, delivers an impressive presence.

Super Illuminator (high-brightness LED light) for maintaining watch readability in the dark
